{"key":"processedPost-8111828","value":{"id":8111828,"first":8111392,"last":8111925,"when":1204845682,"utime":"03/07/08 01:21 AM","content":"Pasteurization of substrates doesn't take a few seconds.  It takes an hour.  The idea is to kill all of the mold spores, and some of the bacteria.  The surviving bacteria keep the substrate 'alive', thus reducing the chances of molds forming.  A few bacteria in a substrate will also improve fruiting, and some species simply will not fruit on a sterile substrate.<br />RR","title":"Re: Why pasteurize for an hour?"}}